Cooper Dominates the Boards with 10 Rebounds in JSU Loss
The Jackson State women's basketball team suffered a 64-47 defeat against Southern in Baton Rouge. Zoe Cooper stood out with 10 rebounds and added 1 point. Despite a strong defensive effort with five blocks, the Tigers faltered after taking an early lead and couldn't close the gap in the second half. Taleah Dilworth led all scorers with 14 points, but the team's offense struggled to keep pace.
- Jackson State recorded five blocks in the game.
- Taleah Dilworth scored 14 points, more than any other player on her team.
- Jackson State held Southern to 39% shooting from the field.
- The Tigers scored only 12 points off of eight Southern turnovers.
Jackson State will look to rebound from this loss as they face Grambling State on Saturday at 2 p.m.
Bottom LineJackson State must improve its offensive consistency and capitalize on defensive efforts if they hope to turn around their season in the upcoming games.
